<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFACFFA1CE11C282FE0DBC48" box="[1292,1308,1272,1292]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="36">¼</emphasis>
10.8 mm) and male paratype (C, UTA A-62347, SVL 
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFACFFA1CA81C36AFABDBC60" box="[412,428,1296,1316]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="36">¼</emphasis>
11.5 mm). All from Talpa de Allende, Jalisco, Mexico, 1771 m. Leaf litter at the type locality where the specimens were collected (D).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C3416565FFACFFA1C853C312FF2FBFCF" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE436EEFFACFFA1C853C312FF2FBFCF" blockId="36.[820,1490,1384,2002]" pageId="36" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFACFFA1C853C312F8E4BCC4" bold="true" box="[846,1013,1384,1408]" pageId="36" pageNumber="36">Comparisons.</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFACFFA1CF0DC313FFFDBCC4" authorityName="Jameson &amp; Streicher &amp; Manuelli &amp; Head &amp; Smith" authorityYear="2022" box="[1040,1260,1384,1408]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rubinus">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFACFFA1CF0DC313FFFDBCC4" box="[1040,1260,1384,1408]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="36">Craugastor rubinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated from 
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFACFFA1C88AC3FCFE8EBCDA" box="[919,1439,1414,1438]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="36">
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFACFFA1C88AC3FCFF48BCDA" authorityName="Jameson &amp; Streicher &amp; Manuelli &amp; Head &amp; Smith" authorityYear="2022" box="[919,1113,1414,1438]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="candelariensis">C. candelariensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFACFFA1CF7BC3FCFFCBBCDA" authorityName="Jameson &amp; Streicher &amp; Manuelli &amp; Head &amp; Smith" authorityYear="2022" box="[1126,1242,1414,1438]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cueyatl">C. cueyatl</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFACFFA1CFF5C3FCFE8ABCDA" baseAuthorityName="Taylor" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[1256,1435,1414,1438]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hobartsmithi">C. hobartsmithi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFACFFA1C829C3DEF8F5BCF8" authorityName="Jameson &amp; Streicher &amp; Manuelli &amp; Head &amp; Smith" authorityYear="2022" box="[820,996,1444,1468]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="portilloensis">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFACFFA1C829C3DEF8F5BCF8" box="[820,996,1444,1468]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="36">C. portilloensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by equal sizes of the inner and outer metatarsal tubercles (unequal sizes in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFACFFA1CFC3C3B8FE44BC9D" authorityName="Jameson &amp; Streicher &amp; Manuelli &amp; Head &amp; Smith" authorityYear="2022" box="[1246,1365,1473,1497]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rubinus">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFACFFA1CFC3C3B8FE44BC9D" box="[1246,1365,1473,1497]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="36">C. rubinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). It can be differentiated from 
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFACFFA1CF0BC3A5FF3EBF50" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="36">
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFACFFA1CF0BC3A5FFBFBCB3" baseAuthorityName="Brocchi" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[1046,1198,1503,1527]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Eleutherodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicanus">C. mexicanus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFACFFA1CFA3C3A5FE40BCB3" baseAuthorityName="Taylor" baseAuthorityYear="1942" box="[1214,1361,1503,1527]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montanus">C. montanus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFACFFA1CE7DC3A5F86EBF50" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="omiltemanus">C. omiltemanus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFACFFA1C892C387FF3ABF50" authorityName="Jameson &amp; Streicher &amp; Manuelli &amp; Head &amp; Smith" authorityYear="2022" box="[911,1067,1532,1556]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="polaclavus">C. polaclavus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFACFFA1CF6CC387FFFBBF50" box="[1137,1258,1532,1556]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Eleutherodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saltator">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFACFFA1CF6CC387FFFBBF50" box="[1137,1258,1532,1556]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="36">C. saltator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of vomerine odontophores (absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFACFFA1CFD1C061FE59BF76" authorityName="Jameson &amp; Streicher &amp; Manuelli &amp; Head &amp; Smith" authorityYear="2022" box="[1228,1352,1562,1586]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rubinus">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFACFFA1CFD1C061FE59BF76" box="[1228,1352,1562,1586]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="36">C. rubinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). It can be differentiated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFACFFA1CF04C042FFB5BF14" authorityName="Jameson &amp; Streicher &amp; Manuelli &amp; Head &amp; Smith" authorityYear="2022" box="[1049,1188,1592,1616]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bitonium">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFACFFA1CF04C042FFB5BF14" box="[1049,1188,1592,1616]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="36">C. bitonium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFACFFA1CFFBC042FE6BBF14" baseAuthorityName="Taylor" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[1254,1402,1592,1616]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pygmaeus">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFACFFA1CFFBC042FE6BBF14" box="[1254,1402,1592,1616]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="36">C. pygmaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of a posterolateral projection of the frontoparietal (present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFACFFA1C8ABC009FF3FBFCF" authorityName="Jameson &amp; Streicher &amp; Manuelli &amp; Head &amp; Smith" authorityYear="2022" box="[950,1070,1651,1675]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="36" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rubinus">
C. 
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFACFFA1C8C4C009FF3FBFCF" box="[985,1070,1651,1675]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="36">rubinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3416565FFACFFA0C853C0EBFBDDBC19" lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="37" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE436EEFFACFFA0C853C0EBF9E3BDED" blockId="36.[820,1490,1384,2002]" lastBlockId="37.[142,813,990,2002]" lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="37" pageId="36" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFACFFA1C853C0EBFF67BFED" bold="true" box="[846,1142,1681,1705]" pageId="36" pageNumber="36">
Description of 
<typeStatus id="54E0884CFFACFFA1CF18C0EBFF60BFED" box="[1029,1137,1681,1705]" pageId="36" pageNumber="36">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
— 
<typeStatus id="54E0884CFFACFFA1CF8EC0EBFFE9BFED" box="[1171,1272,1681,1705]" pageId="36" pageNumber="36">Holotype</typeStatus>
small male (SVL 
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFACFFA1CEA0C0EAFEC0BFED" box="[1469,1489,1680,1705]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="36">¼</emphasis>
<quantity id="4CA39B0BFFACFFA1C829C0D5F889BF83" box="[820,920,1711,1735]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.26" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="12.6">12.6 mm</quantity>
); snout rounded and short (
<quantity id="4CA39B0BFFACFFA1CFDAC0D5FE0ABF82" box="[1223,1307,1711,1735]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
naris–snout; 7% SVL); short eye–nostril distance (
<quantity id="4CA39B0BFFACFFA1CFC8C0B6FE26BFA0" box="[1237,1335,1740,1764]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
; 10% SVL); tympanum 
<quantity id="4CA39B0BFFACFFA1C8ABC090FF1CBE45" box="[950,1037,1770,1794]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
(9.1% SVL); no supratympanic fold or shoulder tubercle; finger length formula III &lt;IV &lt;II &lt;I; single flat palmar tubercle; single flat prepollical tubercle; subarticular tubercles present on all fingers; supernumerary tubercles not present on hand; right arm removed for genetic analysis; toe length formula IV &lt;III &lt;V &lt;II &lt;I; inner metatarsal tubercle larger than outer metatarsal tubercle; subarticular tubercles present on all toes; supernumerary tubercles present on plantar surface; right leg removed for genetic analysis; small dark supracloacal fold; dorsal color in life included brown and grey mottling, orange coloration on arms extending to posterior edge of tympanum (
<figureCitation id="13602A6BFFADFFA0C9A7C24DF831BD0B" box="[698,800,1079,1103]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="36.[142,156,1273,1292]" captionTargetBox="[119,1494,188,1251]" captionTargetId="figure-354@36.[118,1494,188,1251]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIG. 34.—Male holotype of Craugastor rubinus (A, UTA A-62345, SVL ¼ 12.6 mm), male paratype (B, MZFC-HE-35616, SVL ¼ 10.8 mm) and male paratype (C, UTA A-62347, SVL ¼ 11.5 mm). All from Talpa de Allende, Jalisco, Mexico, 1771 m. Leaf litter at the type locality where the specimens were collected (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518655/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">Fig. 34A</figureCitation>
); venter coloration in life included pale, almost blue speckling similar to other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFADFFA0CAACC209F952BDCF" baseAuthorityName="Brocchi" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[433,579,1139,1163]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0CAACC209F952BDCF" box="[433,579,1139,1163]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">C. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
series (
<figureCitation id="13602A6BFFADFFA0C985C209F9F8BDCF" box="[664,745,1139,1163]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="37.[166,180,854,873]" captionTargetBox="[143,812,188,833]" captionTargetId="figure-782@37.[143,812,188,833]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIG. 35.—Ventral coloration in life from some member of the Craugastor mexicanus series. Craugastor rubinus (A, UTA A-62345); C. pygmaeus (B, UTA A-64284), C. cueyatl (C, UTA A-62348). Note varying levels of bluishwhite speckling. A color version of this figure is available online." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518657" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518657/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
); grey in preservative; many bands present on arms and legs.
</paragraph>
<subSection id="E2D42F05FFACFFA1CB06CE76F81BB15A" box="[27,778,2060,2078]" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" type="multiple">
<paragraph id="8BE436EEFFACFFA1CB06CE76F81BB15A" blockId="36.[27,876,2060,2097]" box="[27,778,2060,2078]" pageId="36" pageNumber="36">
Downloaded From: https://bioone.org/journals/Herpetological-Monographs on 
<date id="FFE5102EFFACFFA1C983CE77F81BB15A" box="[670,778,2061,2078]" pageId="36" pageNumber="36" value="2022-05-04">04 May 2022</date>
</paragraph>
</subSection>
<caption id="DF246666FFADFFA0CBBBC52CF9C0BAF5" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518657" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6518657" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518657/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" startId="37.[166,180,854,873]" targetBox="[143,812,188,833]" targetPageId="37">
<paragraph id="8BE436EEFFADFFA0CBBBC52CF9C0BAF5" blockId="37.[142,813,854,945]" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">
FIG. 35.—Ventral coloration in life from some member of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFADFFA0C9D4C52CFBF8BAC4" baseAuthorityName="Brocchi" baseAuthorityYear="1877" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0C9D4C52CFBF8BAC4" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">Craugastor mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
series. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFADFFA0CA32C514FACFBAC5" authorityName="Jameson &amp; Streicher &amp; Manuelli &amp; Head &amp; Smith" authorityYear="2022" box="[303,478,878,897]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rubinus">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0CA32C514FACFBAC5" box="[303,478,878,897]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">Craugastor rubinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(A, UTA A-62345); 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFADFFA0C98AC514F81ABAC5" baseAuthorityName="Taylor" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[663,779,878,897]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pygmaeus">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0C98AC514F81ABAC5" box="[663,779,878,897]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">C. pygmaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(B, UTA A-64284), 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFADFFA0CA01C5FCFA64BADD" authorityName="Jameson &amp; Streicher &amp; Manuelli &amp; Head &amp; Smith" authorityYear="2022" box="[284,373,902,921]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cueyatl">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0CA01C5FCFA64BADD" box="[284,373,902,921]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">C. cueyatl</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(C, UTA A-62348). Note varying levels of bluishwhite speckling. Acolor version of this figure is available online.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BE436EEFFADFFA0CBB4C2D5FBDDBC19" blockId="37.[142,813,990,2002]" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0CBB4C2D5FAC4BD83" bold="true" box="[169,469,1199,1223]" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">
Variations in 
<typeStatus id="54E0884CFFADFFA0CA4BC2D5FAC1BD83" box="[342,464,1199,1223]" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">paratypes</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
—Body sizes (SVL) 
<quantity id="4CA39B0BFFADFFA0C9D8C2D5F83DBD83" box="[709,812,1199,1223]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.08" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="10.8">10.8 mm</quantity>
(MZFC-HE-35616), 
<quantity id="4CA39B0BFFADFFA0CA60C2B7FAF2BDA0" box="[381,483,1229,1253]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="11.5">11.5 mm</quantity>
(UTA A-62347); eye–nostril distance both 10% SVL; tympanic ratios both 9%; dorsal color pattern mottled (MZFC-HE-35616; 
<figureCitation id="13602A6BFFADFFA0C974C373F9DABC65" box="[617,715,1289,1313]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="36.[142,156,1273,1292]" captionTargetBox="[119,1494,188,1251]" captionTargetId="figure-354@36.[118,1494,188,1251]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIG. 34.—Male holotype of Craugastor rubinus (A, UTA A-62345, SVL ¼ 12.6 mm), male paratype (B, MZFC-HE-35616, SVL ¼ 10.8 mm) and male paratype (C, UTA A-62347, SVL ¼ 11.5 mm). All from Talpa de Allende, Jalisco, Mexico, 1771 m. Leaf litter at the type locality where the specimens were collected (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518655/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">Fig. 34B</figureCitation>
) or with dark stripe extending from snout to flank (UTA A-62347, 
<figureCitation id="13602A6BFFADFFA0C81CC35DFBAEBC19" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="36.[142,156,1273,1292]" captionTargetBox="[119,1494,188,1251]" captionTargetId="figure-354@36.[118,1494,188,1251]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIG. 34.—Male holotype of Craugastor rubinus (A, UTA A-62345, SVL ¼ 12.6 mm), male paratype (B, MZFC-HE-35616, SVL ¼ 10.8 mm) and male paratype (C, UTA A-62347, SVL ¼ 11.5 mm). All from Talpa de Allende, Jalisco, Mexico, 1771 m. Leaf litter at the type locality where the specimens were collected (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518655/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">Fig. 34C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3416565FFADFFA0CBB4C318F9BCBCF2" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BE436EEFFADFFA0CBB4C318F9BCBCF2" blockId="37.[142,813,990,2002]" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0CBB4C318FA57BC3E" bold="true" box="[169,326,1378,1402]" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">Distribution.</emphasis>
—Known only from the 
<typeStatus id="54E0884CFFADFFA0C964C319F9B9BC3F" box="[633,680,1379,1403]" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
locality in Jalisco (Talpa de Allende), habitat of pine–oak forest at the southern extent of the Sierra Madre Occidental.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3416565FFADFFA0CBB4C3C7F9D3BF6A" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE436EEFFADFFA0CBB4C3C7F9D3BF6A" blockId="37.[142,813,990,2002]" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0CBB4C3C7FA22BC91" bold="true" box="[169,307,1469,1493]" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">Etymology.</emphasis>
—The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0CBCFC3A0FA3FBCB6" box="[210,302,1498,1522]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFADFFA0CBCFC3A0FA3BBCB6" authorityName="Jameson &amp; Streicher &amp; Manuelli &amp; Head &amp; Smith" authorityYear="2022" box="[210,298,1498,1522]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rubinus">rubinus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
which means ruby. This name is inspired by the garnet mines found near the 
<typeStatus id="54E0884CFFADFFA0C90EC383F953BF55" box="[531,578,1529,1553]" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
locality of Talpa de Allende in the Sierra Madre Occidental of Jalisco.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3416565FFADFFA0CBB4C04EF878B823" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE436EEFFADFFA0CBB4C04EF9D9BFA6" blockId="37.[142,813,990,2002]" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0CBB4C04EFA48BF08" bold="true" box="[169,345,1588,1612]" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">Phylogenetics.</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFADFFA0CA6EC04FF943BF08" authorityName="Jameson &amp; Streicher &amp; Manuelli &amp; Head &amp; Smith" authorityYear="2022" box="[371,594,1588,1612]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rubinus">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0CA6EC04FF943BF08" box="[371,594,1588,1612]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">Craugastor rubinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was strongly supported as monophyletic in the concatenated analysis (ML 
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0C805C02BF83DBF2E" box="[792,812,1617,1642]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">¼</emphasis>
99; BAYES 
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0CA0BC015FA3BBFCC" box="[278,298,1647,1672]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">¼</emphasis>
1.0; 
<figureCitation id="13602A6BFFADFFA0CA7BC00AFABBBFCC" box="[358,426,1648,1672]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="8.[142,156,1857,1876]" captionTargetBox="[295,1312,189,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-1@8.[294,1312,187,1835]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIG. 3.—Concatenated Maximum Likelihood analyses of two mitochondrial (12S and 16S) and two nuclear (RAG1 and TYR) gene fragments sequenced from the Craugastor mexicanus series (total of 2230 base pairs). Node values correspond to bootstrap support from Maximum Likelihood analysis and posterior probabilities from a Bayesian analysis of the same data set, respectively. Support values are not reported for nodes that had,50/0.50. NS indicates no support in the Bayesian analysis for a depicted relationship. Locality abbreviations are as follows: COL ¼ Colima, HID ¼ Hidalgo, GRO ¼ Guerrero, JAL ¼ Jalisco, MEX ¼ Estado de México, OAX ¼ Oaxaca, PUE ¼ Puebla, and VER ¼ Veracruz." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518593/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). The new species is also strongly supported as the sister taxon of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFADFFA0CAE1C0F4F9C0BFE2" baseAuthorityName="Taylor" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[508,721,1678,1702]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hobartsmithi">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0CAE1C0F4F91EBFE1" box="[508,527,1678,1701]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">C</emphasis>
. cf. 
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0C959C0F4F9C0BFE2" box="[580,721,1678,1702]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">hobartsmithi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(ML 
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0C805C0F7F83DBFE2" box="[792,812,1677,1702]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">¼</emphasis>
100; BAYES 
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0CA00C0D1FA20BF80" box="[285,305,1707,1732]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">¼</emphasis>
1.0). 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFADFFA0CA6DC0D6F959BF80" authorityName="Jameson &amp; Streicher &amp; Manuelli &amp; Head &amp; Smith" authorityYear="2022" box="[368,584,1708,1732]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rubinus">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0CA6DC0D6F959BF80" box="[368,584,1708,1732]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">Craugastor rubinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is separated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFADFFA0C80EC0D6FA2EBFA6" baseAuthorityName="Taylor" baseAuthorityYear="1936" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hobartsmithi">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0C80EC0D6F837BF87" box="[787,806,1708,1731]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">C</emphasis>
. cf. 
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0CBAFC0B0FA2EBFA6" box="[178,319,1738,1762]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">hobartsmithi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a 
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0CA9DC0B1FA9EBFA6" box="[384,399,1739,1762]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">P</emphasis>
-distance of 3.4% (
<tableCitation id="C6D90355FFADFFA0C97FC0B0F9AABFA6" box="[610,699,1738,1762]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="7.[169,182,188,207]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="TABLE 4.—Genetic P-distances derived from the concatenated alignment 2230 base pairs of 12S and 16S (mtDNA) þ RAG1 and TYR (nDNA) for species contained within the Craugastor mexicanus series. Bolded distances on diagonal are within species P-distances (if more than a single individual was used to estimate mean genetic distance)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF246666FF8FFF82CBB4C6C6FAA2B9BB" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" tableUuid="DF246666FF8FFF82CBB4C6C6FAA2B9BB">Table 4</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE436EEFFADFFA0CBB4C092F878B823" blockId="37.[142,813,990,2002]" lastBlockId="37.[844,1515,188,359]" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0CBB4C092FA0CBE44" bold="true" box="[169,285,1768,1792]" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">Remarks.</emphasis>
—The skull of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFADFFA0CADCC092F926BE44" authorityName="Jameson &amp; Streicher &amp; Manuelli &amp; Head &amp; Smith" authorityYear="2022" box="[449,567,1768,1792]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rubinus">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0CADCC092F926BE44" box="[449,567,1768,1792]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">C. rubinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to that of 
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0C80EC092FADABE5A" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFADFFA0C80EC092FA0FBE5A" baseAuthorityName="Taylor" baseAuthorityYear="1936" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hobartsmithi">C. hobartsmithi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFADFFA0CA2CC17CFAD6BE5A" baseAuthorityName="Taylor" baseAuthorityYear="1942" box="[305,455,1798,1822]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montanus">C. montanus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFADFFA0C90DC17CF9B7BE5A" baseAuthorityName="Taylor" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[528,678,1798,1822]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pygmaeus">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0C90DC17CF9B7BE5A" box="[528,678,1798,1822]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">C. pygmaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with more posteriorly placed anterior suture of the frontoparietal and prootic than in other species. The 
<typeStatus id="54E0884CFFADFFA0C90AC138F957BE1E" box="[535,582,1858,1882]" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
series was collected from the leaf litter surrounding a mountain stream. The male 
<typeStatus id="54E0884CFFADFFA0CB93C107FBFCBED1" box="[142,237,1917,1941]" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">holotype</typeStatus>
has slightly pigmented testes. Afemale 
<typeStatus id="54E0884CFFADFFA0C9DBC104F839BED2" box="[710,808,1918,1942]" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">paratype</typeStatus>
, UTA A-62345, has large, pigmented ovaries. This species may co-occur with 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFADFFA0CA73C1C0F931BE95" baseAuthorityName="Taylor" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[366,544,1977,2001]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hobartsmithi">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0CA73C1C0F931BE95" box="[366,544,1977,2001]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">C. hobartsmithi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Jalisco. Despite the small genetic distances separating 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFADFFA0CFF8C6C7FE70B990" authorityName="Jameson &amp; Streicher &amp; Manuelli &amp; Head &amp; Smith" authorityYear="2022" box="[1253,1377,188,212]" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rubinus">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0CFF8C6C7FE70B990" box="[1253,1377,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">C. rubinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B4D6DFFADFFA0CEBAC6C7F8CDB9B5" baseAuthorityName="Taylor" baseAuthorityYear="1936" class="Amphibia" family="Craugastoridae" genus="Craugastor" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hobartsmithi">
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0CEBAC6C7FEABB990" box="[1447,1466,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">C</emphasis>
. cf. 
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0C851C6A3F8CDB9B5" box="[844,988,217,241]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">hobartsmithi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B92FEAFCFFADFFA0C8C1C6A3F8F1B9B5" box="[988,992,217,241]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="37">,</emphasis>
there are many skeletal and morphological differences between these two species, including relative metatarsal tubercle sizes, condition of the posterolateral projection of frontoparietal, and relative snout length (
<tableCitation id="C6D90355FFADFFA0CEB7C74BF84DB823" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="14.[846,859,803,823]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="TABLE 6.—Select characteristics of species in the Craugastor mexicanus series. X indicates presence, O indicates absence, and? indicates uncertainty. If greater than one, number of specimens examined is indicated in parentheses." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF246666FF86FF8BC853C559FF05BA0B" pageId="37" pageNumber="37" tableUuid="DF246666FF86FF8BC853C559FF05BA0B">Table 6</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
